The paper presents a statistical model for travel time estimation using vehicle trajectories obtained from low frequency GPS probes. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with transportation systems, which could place it in the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of statistical models and estimation techniques, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also deals with network structures and correlations, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with spatial and temporal variations, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
